member.example:
There are many scenarios where controlling profiler from the profilee is useful. One of these cases is profiling code which is
slow only occasionally, not always. In this case you might use the scheme displayed below:

public void YourSlowFunction()
{
  long ticks = DateTime.Now.Ticks;
  CPUProfiler.Start();

  try
  {
    // Your code which might be slow and might be not.
  }
  finally
  {
    // This invocation has taken significant time and needs to be profiled
    if (DateTime.Now.Ticks - ticks > Threshold)
      CPUProfiler.StopAndSaveSnapshot();  
    else
      CPUProfiler.StopAndDropSnapshot();       
  }
}


This way you can get snapshot each time when your code executes longer than the specified threshold value.
